InterContinental Hotels Group Plc (IHG)  is
taking 24 percent of a joint venture with Duet  India  Hotels
Group to build 19 Holiday Inn Express hotels in India during the
next five years, the Financial Times reported, citing Richard Solomons, IHGâ€™s finance director.  IHG is putting $30 million of its own cash into the
venture, to be paid over three years, the newspaper said.  The U.K. company plans to have 150 hotels in India by 2020,
